      <section class="biography" id="biography">
        <h1 class="label">Biography</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Rachel Glennerster was appointed Chief Economist at the Department for International Development in January 2018.</p>
</div>
      </section>

      <div class="current-roles" id="current-roles">
          <section class="role_appointment role" id="role_appointment_4826">
            <h1 id="chief-economist">Chief Economist</h1>
            <div class="govspeak">
<p>The Chief Economist is responsible for:</p>

<ul>
  <li>providing economic advice to Ministers, senior officials, and country offices</li>
  <li>ensuring DFID policies and investment decisions are informed by rigorous evidence</li>
  <li>overseeing the Quality Assurance Unit which reviews large business cases prior to submission to Ministers</li>
  <li>supporting economists throughout the department by providing opportunities to stay up to date with developments in the economic discipline</li>
  <li>working with other Chief Economists to contribute to a vibrant Government Economic Service and to address cross departmental issues</li>
</ul>
</div>
            <div class="read-more">
                <p class="js-hide-other-departments organisations-name-list">
  <a class="organisation-link" href="/government/organisations/department-for-international-development">Department for International Development</a>
</p>

            </div>
</section>      </div>




